HB 165 Original 2026 Regular Session Hebert
Abstract: Provides for the creation of a new lottery game with proceeds benefitting
veterans.
Present constitution provides that lottery proceeds shall be appropriated only for the purpose
of the minimum foundation program and no more than $500,000 for services related to
problem gaming.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution and adds a provision
allowing the legislature to approve a new lottery game. The proceeds of the new lottery
game created pursuant to proposed constitutional amendment would be used for the benefit
of La. resident military veterans and their families.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held Nov. 3, 2026.
(Amends Const. Art. XII, §6(A)(1))
